08/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Bulgarian Red Cross and citizens' associations have joined efforts in a mass action to help the children of Beslan, Russia, victims of last weekâ€™s school hostage tragedy.
President Georgi Parvanov's plane is carrying clothing, books and medical supplies to the region Wednesday (8 September).
Parvanov has offered to fly up to 200 children back to Bulgaria to rest at sea and mountain accommodations there.
In other news, Bulgaria is being warned again over continuing intellectual piracy problems.
The World Association of Recording Industries said on Tuesday Sofia would face sanctions unless the production of pirated CDs and DVDs is curbed.
